\title{Domain Name Brainstormer}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Generates creative domain name ideas for your project and checks availability}

\subtree{
\title{Domain Name Brainstormer}
\p{This skill helps you find the perfect domain name for your project by generating creative options and checking what's actually available to register.}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\ul{
\li{Starting a new project or company}
\li{Launching a product or service}
\li{Creating a personal brand or portfolio site}
\li{Rebranding an existing project}
\li{Registering a domain for a side project}
\li{Finding available alternatives when your first choice is taken}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{What This Skill Does}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Understands Your Project}: Analyzes what you're building and who it's for}
\li{\strong{Generates Creative Names}: Creates relevant, memorable domain options}
\li{\strong{Checks Availability}: Verifies which domains are actually available across multiple TLDs}
\li{\strong{Multiple Extensions}: Suggests .com, .io, .dev, .ai, .app, and more}
\li{\strong{Provides Alternatives}: Offers variations if top choices are taken}
\li{\strong{Branding Insights}: Explains why certain names work well}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{How to Use}
\subtree{
\title{Basic Brainstorming}
\pre{\startverb
I'm building a project management tool for remote teams. 
Suggest domain names.
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
Help me brainstorm domain names for a personal finance app
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Specific Preferences}
\pre{\startverb
I need a domain name for my AI writing assistant. 
Prefer short names with .ai or .io extension.
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{With Keywords}
\pre{\startverb
Suggest domain names using the words "pixel" or "studio" 
for my design agency
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example}
\p{\strong{User}: "I'm building a tool for developers to share code snippets. Suggest creative domain names."}

\p{\strong{Output}:}

\pre{\startverb
Analyzing your project...
Target audience: Developers
Key features: Code sharing, snippets, collaboration

🎯 Domain Name Suggestions

## Available (.com)
1. ✓ snippetbox.com - Clear, memorable, available!
   Why: Directly describes the product, easy to remember

2. ✓ codeclip.com - Short and snappy
   Why: Implies quick code sharing, only 8 characters

3. ✓ devpaste.com - Developer-focused
   Why: Familiar to devs (like pastebin), clear purpose

## Available (Alternative TLDs)
4. ✓ snippet.dev - Perfect extension for developers
   Why: .dev extension signals developer tool

5. ✓ codebox.io - Tech-forward
   Why: .io popular with tech startups, clean name

6. ✓ sharecode.app - Descriptive
   Why: .app extension, clearly states the action

## Premium/Taken (.com)
- codeshare.com (Taken, est. $2,500)
- snippets.com (Taken, premium domain)

## Recommendations

🏆 Top Pick: snippet.dev
- Perfect for developer audience
- Short and memorable  
- .dev extension adds credibility
- Available now!

🥈 Runner-up: snippetbox.com
- .com is universally recognized
- Slightly longer but descriptive
- Great brandability

Next steps:
1. Register your favorite before someone else does!
2. Want me to check more variations?
3. Need help with logo ideas for these names?
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Inspired by:} Ben Aiad's use case from Lenny's Newsletter}
}

\subtree{
\title{Domain Naming Tips}
\subtree{
\title{What Makes a Good Domain}
\p{✓ \strong{Short}: Under 15 characters ideal ✓ \strong{Memorable}: Easy to recall and spell ✓ \strong{Pronounceable}: Can be said in conversation ✓ \strong{Descriptive}: Hints at what you do ✓ \strong{Brandable}: Unique enough to stand out ✓ \strong{No hyphens}: Easier to share verbally}
}

\subtree{
\title{TLD Guide}
\ul{
\li{\strong{.com}: Universal, trusted, great for businesses}
\li{\strong{.io}: Tech startups, developer tools}
\li{\strong{.dev}: Developer-focused products}
\li{\strong{.ai}: AI/ML products}
\li{\strong{.app}: Mobile or web applications}
\li{\strong{.co}: Alternative to .com}
\li{\strong{.xyz}: Modern, creative projects}
\li{\strong{.design}: Creative/design agencies}
\li{\strong{.tech}: Technology companies}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Advanced Features}
\subtree{
\title{Check Similar Variations}
\pre{\startverb
Check availability for "codebase" and similar variations 
across .com, .io, .dev
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Industry-Specific}
\pre{\startverb
Suggest domain names for a sustainable fashion brand, 
checking .eco and .fashion TLDs
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Multilingual Options}
\pre{\startverb
Brainstorm domain names in English and Spanish for 
a language learning app
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Competitor Analysis}
\pre{\startverb
Show me domain patterns used by successful project 
management tools, then suggest similar available ones
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example Workflows}
\subtree{
\title{Startup Launch}
\ol{
\li{Describe your startup idea}
\li{Get 10-15 domain suggestions across TLDs}
\li{Review availability and pricing}
\li{Pick top 3 favorites}
\li{Register immediately}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Personal Brand}
\ol{
\li{Share your name and profession}
\li{Get variations (firstname.com, firstnamelastname.dev, etc.)}
\li{Check social media handle availability too}
\li{Register consistent brand across platforms}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Product Naming}
\ol{
\li{Describe product and target market}
\li{Get creative, brandable names}
\li{Check trademark conflicts}
\li{Verify domain and social availability}
\li{Test names with target audience}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tips for Success}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Act Fast}: Good domains get taken quickly}
\li{\strong{Register Variations}: Get .com and .io to protect brand}
\li{\strong{Avoid Numbers}: Hard to communicate verbally}
\li{\strong{Check Social Media}: Make sure @username is available too}
\li{\strong{Say It Out Loud}: Test if it's easy to pronounce}
\li{\strong{Check Trademarks}: Ensure no legal conflicts}
\li{\strong{Think Long-term}: Will it still make sense in 5 years?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pricing Context}
\p{When suggesting domains, I'll note:}

\ul{
\li{Standard domains: ~$10-15/year}
\li{Premium TLDs (.io, .ai): ~$30-50/year}
\li{Taken domains: Market price if listed}
\li{Premium domains: $hundreds to $thousands}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Related Tools}
\p{After picking a domain:}

\ul{
\li{Check logo design options}
\li{Verify social media handles}
\li{Research trademark availability}
\li{Plan brand identity colors/fonts}
}
}
}